The crystal structure of Cs4PbX6 consists of caged PbX6 octahedra, isolated by interspersed Cs–X bridges21. Two types of Cs sites are present: the Cs(1) site form an alternating octahedra with PbX6, whereas the Cs(2) trigonal prisms share one triangular face to form infinite [CsPbX6]n3– chains along the [001] direction24. The synthesized samples were highly crystalline matching with the rhombohedral Cs4PbX6 phase (X = Br, Br/Cl, and Cl; space group: R3¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
